HEADWORD: biofeedback
<hw>bi`o*feed"back</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a training program in which a
person is given information about physiological processes (heart rate or
blood pressure) that is not normally available with the goal of gaining
conscious control of them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bioflavinoid</ent>⟦br⟧
